confined by his profe&s;&s;ion to a
di&s;tant kingdom, as her protector; but it
gave her comfort to know, that there was,
at lea&s;t, one per&s;on in the world, who would &s;ymphathize in her
afflictions, and
who&s;e wi&s;hes would fly eagerly to relea&s;e
