<P>&startq;I cannot boa&s;t of a learned education,
niece, &s;uch as your father thought proper
to give you, and, therefore, do not pre|tend
to under&s;tand all the&s;e fine &s;peeches
about happine&s;s. I mu&s;t be contented to
under&s;tand only common &s;en&s;e, and happy
<PB N="114" REF="116">
would it have been for you and your father,
