di&s;covery, which had ju&s;t been forced upon
her, of Montoni's unworthine&s;s &s;he had
now to add, that of the cruel vanity, for
the gratification of which her aunt was
about to &s;acrifice her; of the effrontery
and cunning, with which, at the time that
&s;he meditated the &s;acrifice, &s;he boa&s;ted of
her tenderne&s;s, or in&s;ulted her victim: and
