<L>Oft deep-drawn &s;ighs his anxious wi&s;h proclaim</L>
<L>To reach, again, his happy cottage door;</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>For there, his wife, his little children, dwell;</L>
<L>Their &s;miles &s;hall pay the toil of many an hour:</L>
<L>Ev'n now warm tears to expectation &s;well,</L>
<L>As fancy o'er his mind extends her pow'r.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<PB N="119" REF="121">
<L>A death-like &s;tillne&s;s reign'd, where once the &s;ong,</L>
<L>The &s;ong of heroes, wak'd the midnight air,</L>
