its door unclo&s;e &s;he forgot all other cau&s;e
of alarm, and retreated towards the corri|dor.
Here &s;he endeavoured to make her
e&s;cape, but, on opening the door, was very
near falling over a per&s;on, who lay on the
floor without. She &s;creamed, and would
<PB N="369" REF="371">
have pa&s;&s;ed, but her trembling frame re|fu&s;ed
to &s;upport her; and the moment, in
which &s;he leaned again&s;t the wall of the
