of Annette. Fear in&s;tantly yielded to
&s;urpri&s;e. She &s;poke in vain to the poor
girl, who remained &s;en&s;ele&s;s on the floor,
and then, lo&s;ing all con&s;ciou&s;ne&s;s of ther own
