&startq;I would not &s;liip in the room,
now, for a tho&s;and &s;equins!&endq;</P>
<P>Wearied and di&s;appointed, Emily fir&s;t
$idiculed, though &s;he &s;hared, her fears, and
then tried to &s;ooth them; but neither at|tempt
&s;ucceeded, and the girl per&s;i&s;ted in
