to proceed from one of the chambers, open|ing
into the gallery. It in&s;tantly occurred
to her, that Madame Montoni might be
there confined, and &s;he advanced to the
door to &s;peak, but was checked by con&s;i
dering, that &s;he was, perhaps, going to com|mit
<PB N="425" REF="427">
her&s;elf to a &s;tranger, who might di&s;co|ver
