whoever it was, &s;eemed to be in afflic|tion,
it did not follow, that he was a pri|&s;oner.</P>
<P>While the&s;e thoughts pa&s;&s;ed over her mind,
and left her &s;till in her&s;itation, the voice
&s;poke again, and, calling &startq;Ludovico,&endq; &s;he
then perceived it to be that of Annette; on
